cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CV

This paper presents a method for scaling SVM and LAD to large-scale problems, which is a common challenge in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which focuses on the development and analysis of algorithms for learning from data. 

The paper also involves variational inequalities and data reduction techniques, which are related to numerical analysis and optimization. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely categories. 

Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on both synthetic and real data sets, which suggests that it may be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as well.
